<!--
  Intentionally empty optional config.

  Its sole purpose is to let the main plugin DECLARE an optional dependency on
  `com.intellij.modules.java` (the Java plugin) WITHOUT loading any extension.

  Why it's needed: base and Scala code of Cucumber+ references Java-plugin classes
  (e.g. com.intellij.debugger.DebuggerManagerEx in JavaTzatzikiExtensionPoint /
  ScalaTzatzikiExtensionPoint, and CreateFromUsageUtils in JavaStepDefinitionCreator).
  The Marketplace verifier (and the runtime classloader) must therefore see modules.java
  in the dependency closure to resolve them.

  Why it's SEPARATE from plugin-withJava.xml: the crash-prone cucumber Java extensions
  (TzGherkinJavaExtension : CucumberJavaExtension) live in plugin-withJava.xml, gated on the
  `cucumber-java` PLUGIN — so they only load when cucumber-java is installed. This file is gated
  on modules.java only (present in any IDEA), loads nothing, and so never triggers that crash.
-->
<idea-plugin>
</idea-plugin>
